module_people_also_ask.title: Why should we get vaccinated for COVID-19?

stripped_html.HTML: Higher vaccination rates makes outbreaks much less likely. It also reduces the need for preventive measures, such as border closures and travel restrictions.

module_people_also_ask.title: Can I still get Covid after the vaccine?

stripped_html.HTML: If someone is unlucky to get Covid after having been vaccinated and you can still, in some cases, get Covid after you get vaccinated, even though your chances seem to be lower, it is likely you will experience a much milder disease.1 July 2021

module_people_also_ask.title: What are some common side effects of the COVID-19 vaccine?

stripped_html.HTML:
Common reactions to vaccination include:
• pain, redness and/or swelling where you received the needle
• mild fever
• headache.

17 May 2021

module_people_also_ask.title: Can vaccinated people get long Covid?

stripped_html.HTML: It is theoretically possible for a fully vaccinated person to get long Covid. But doctors contend that it doesn't appear to be a significant risk. Coronavirus infections leading to long-haul Covid-19 in fully vaccinated people are probably very rare, experts say.19 hours ago
